Package com.ibm.wcs.annotationservice

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AnnotatorWrapper
    Interface encapsulating the major functionality of an annotator runtime supported by the Annotator Module: the ability to execute the annotator on a given document, and the ability to interrupt execution; all instances of annotator runtimes supported by the Annotation Module implement this interface
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AnnotationService
    Class that encapsulates instantiation and invocation of multiple annotator bundles.
    AnnotationServiceConstants
    Various constants used by the Annotation Service.
    AnnotatorBundle
    Class encapsulating the instantiation of an annotator bundle, and the execution on a single document.
    AnnotatorBundle.RawAnnotationOutputRecord
    A wrapper class for annotation result of Low-level Java API result
    AnnotatorResources
    Class to export annotator model for recreating operatorGraph
    AnnotatorWrapperFactory
    Factory class to create an instance of AnnotatorWrapper.
    AnnotatorWrapperImpl
    Super class encapsulating common functionality across different implementations of the Annotator Module runtime functionality; all implementations supported by the Annotation Modules (SystemT, UIMA, SIRE) inherit from this class.
    AnnotatorWrapperSystemT  
    ExecuteParams
    Class that encapsulates various parameters for executing AnnotatorBundle#invoke() on a single document.
    InterruptResponse
    Object to store whether the annotation execution was interrupted and communicate that to the caller.
